  %body
    #header
      %ul
        %li.title
          %a(href="http://lab.dev.concord.org/components/components.html") About Atoms
      %ul.right
        %li
        %img#fullscreen(class="alignleft size-full wp-image-1880" src="../../resources/layout/fullscreen.gif" width="32" height="32")
    #viz
      %ul
        %li.top
          #molecule-container
          #controls
            #playback
            %ul
              %li{:style=>"display: none"}
                %fieldset
                  %legend Molecules
                  %select(id="select-molecule-number")
                    %option(value="50" selected) 50
          
        %li
          #thermometer
          #therm_text
        %li.top
          #description-right
            %p
              A computational simulation of a collection of simple atoms with the forces between
              the atoms modeled with both the Lennard-Jones Potential which models Pauli repulsion at 
              short ranges and the attractive van der Waals forces that act over longer-ranges.
            %p
              Adijust this slider to vary the strength of the 
              %b van der Waals attraction:
            .component_group
              .slider_container
                .left_half
                  stronger
                .right_half
                  weaker
                .content
                  #attraction_slider{  'data-label' => "attractive force"}
                .below
                  Attractive Force
            %p
              You can also change the 
              %b temperature 
              of the simulation by adjusting this slider:
            .component_group
              .slider_container
                .left_half
                  colder
                .right_half
                  hotter
                .content
                  #temperature_slider{  'data-label' => "temperature"}
                .below
                  Temperature
            %p
              Charges of +1 or -1 are evenly distributed among the atoms. When the Coulomb particle 
              force interaction checkbox is enabled atoms with the opposite charges experience an 
              attractive force. Atoms with a positive charge appear green, atoms with a negative 
              charge appear red.
            .component_group
              .slider_container
                .left_half
                  Force Interactions
                .right_half
                .content
                  %div{:style=> "width: 200px; height: 20px; display: inline-block; margin: 5px"}
                    Coulomb
                    %input(id="coulomb-forces-checkbox" type="checkbox" checked)
                .below
                  %input(id="lennard-jones-forces-checkbox" type="checkbox" checked)

